{"DRAB":[{"def":"A low, sluttish woman.","pos":""},{"def":"A lewd wench; a strumpet.","pos":""}],"DRABBER":[{"def":"One who associates with drabs; a wencher.","pos":""}],"DRABBET":[{"def":"A coarse linen fabric, or duck.","pos":""}],"DRABBISH":[{"def":"Somewhat drab in color.","pos":""}],"DRABBLE":[{"def":"To draggle; to wet and befoul by draggling; as, to drabble a gown or cloak.","pos":""}],"DRABBLE-TAIL":[{"def":"A draggle-tail; a slattern.","pos":""}],"DRABBLER":[{"def":"A piece of canvas fastened by lacing to the bonnet of a sail, to give it a greater depth, or more drop.","pos":""}],"DRACAENA":[{"def":"A genus of liliaceous plants with woody stems and funnel-shaped flowers.","pos":""}],"DRACANTH":[{"def":"A kind of gum; -- called also gum tragacanth, or tragacanth.","pos":""}],"DRACHMA":[{"def":"A silver coin among the ancient Greeks, having a different value in different States and at different periods.","pos":""},{"def":"A gold and silver coin of modern Greece worth 19.","pos":""}],"DRACO":[{"def":"The Dragon, a northern constellation within which is the north pole of the ecliptic.","pos":""},{"def":"A genus of lizards.","pos":""}],"DRACONIAN":[{"def":"Pertaining to Draco, a famous lawgiver of Athens, 621 b.","pos":""}],"DRACONIC":[{"def":"Relating to Draco, the Athenian lawgiver; or to the constellation Draco; or to dragon's blood.","pos":""}],"DRACONIN":[{"def":"A red resin forming the essential basis of dragon's blood; -- called also dracin.","pos":""}],"DRACONTIC":[{"def":"Belonging to that space of time in which the moon performs one revolution, from ascending node to ascending node.","pos":""}],"DRACONTINE":[{"def":"Belonging to a dragon.","pos":""}],"DRADGE":[{"def":"Inferior ore, separated from the better by cobbing.","pos":""}],"DRAFF":[{"def":"Refuse; lees; dregs; the wash given to swine or cows; hogwash; waste matter.","pos":""}],"DRAFFISH":[{"def":"Worthless; draffy.","pos":""}],"DRAFFY":[{"def":"Dreggy; waste; worthless.","pos":""}],"DRAFT":[{"def":"Pertaining to, or used for, drawing or pulling (as vehicles, loads, etc.","pos":""},{"def":"Relating to, or characterized by, a draft, or current of air.","pos":""}],"DRAFTSMAN":[{"def":"See Draughtsman.","pos":""}],"DRAG":[{"def":"A confection; a comfit; a drug.","pos":""}],"DRAGANTINE":[{"def":"A mucilage obtained from, or containing, gun tragacanth.","pos":""}],"DRAGBAR":[{"def":"Same as Drawbar (b).","pos":""}],"DRAGEES":[{"def":"Sugar-coated medicines.","pos":""}],"DRAGGLE":[{"def":"To wet and soil by dragging on the ground, mud, or wet grass; to drabble; to trail.","pos":""}],"DRAGGLE-TAIL":[{"def":"A slattern who suffers her gown to trail in the mire; a drabble-tail.","pos":""}],"DRAGGLE-TAILED":[{"def":"Untidy; sluttish; slatternly.","pos":""}],"DRAGMAN":[{"def":"A fisherman who uses a dragnet.","pos":""}],"DRAGNET":[{"def":"A net to be drawn along the bottom of a body of water, as in fishing.","pos":""}],"DRAGOMAN":[{"def":"An interpreter; -- so called in the Levant and other parts of the East.","pos":""}],"DRAGON":[{"def":"A fabulous animal, generally represented as a monstrous winged serpent or lizard, with a crested head and enormous claws, and regarded as very powerful and ferocious.","pos":""},{"def":"A constellation of the northern hemisphere figured as a dragon; Draco.","pos":""}],"DRAGONET":[{"def":"A small British marine fish (Callionymuslyra); -- called also yellow sculpin, fox, and gowdie.","pos":""}],"DRAGONISH":[{"def":"resembling a dragon.","pos":""}],"DRAGONNADE":[{"def":"The severe persecution of French Protestants under Louis XIV.","pos":""},{"def":"See Dragon's blood, Dragon's head, etc.","pos":""}],"DRAGOON":[{"def":"Formerly, a soldier who was taught and armed to serve either on horseback or on foot; now, a mounted soldier; a cavalry man.","pos":""}],"DRAIL":[{"def":"To trail; to draggle.","pos":""}],"DRAIN":[{"def":"To draw off by degrees; to cause to flow gradually out or off; hence, to cause the exhaustion of.","pos":""},{"def":"To exhaust of liquid contents by drawing them off; to make gradually dry or empty; to remove surface water, as from streets, by gutters, etc.","pos":""}],"DRAINABLE":[{"def":"Capable of being drained.","pos":""}],"DRAINAGE":[{"def":"The system of drains and their operation, by which superfluous water is removed from towns, railway beds, mines, and other works.","pos":""},{"def":"The act, process, or means of drawing off the pus or fluids from a wound, abscess, etc.","pos":""}],"DRAINE":[{"def":"The missel thrush.","pos":""}],"DRAINER":[{"def":"One who, or that which, drains.","pos":""}],"DRAINING":[{"def":"The art of carrying off surplus water, as from land.","pos":""}],"DRAINPIPE":[{"def":"A pipe used for carrying off surplus water.","pos":""}],"DRAINTILE":[{"def":"A hollow tile used in making drains; -- called also draining tile.","pos":""}],"DRAINTRAP":[{"def":"See 4th Trap, 5.","pos":""}],"DRAKE":[{"def":"The male of the duck kind.","pos":""}],"DRAKESTONE":[{"def":"A flat stone so thrown along the surface of water as to skip from point to point before it sinks; also, the sport of so throwing stones; -- sometimes called ducks and drakes.","pos":""}],"DRAM":[{"def":"A Persian daric.","pos":""}],"DRAMA":[{"def":"Of or pertaining to the drama; appropriate to, or having the qualities of, a drama; theatrical; vivid.","pos":""}],"DRAMATICALLY":[{"def":"In a dramatic manner; theatrically; vividly.","pos":""}],"DRAMATIS PERSONAE":[{"def":"The actors in a drama or play.","pos":""}],"DRAMATIST":[{"def":"The author of a dramatic composition; a writer of plays.","pos":""}],"DRAMATIZABLE":[{"def":"Capable of being dramatized.","pos":""}],"DRAMATIZATION":[{"def":"Act of dramatizing.","pos":""}],"DRAMATIZE":[{"def":"To compose in the form of the drama; to represent in a drama; to adapt to dramatic representation; as, to dramatize a novel, or an historical episode.","pos":""}],"DRAMATURGIC":[{"def":"Relating to dramaturgy.","pos":""}],"DRAMATURGIST":[{"def":"One versed in dramaturgy.","pos":""}],"DRAMATURGY":[{"def":"The art of dramatic composition and representation.","pos":""}],"DRAMMING":[{"def":"The practice of drinking drams.","pos":""}],"DRAMSELLER":[{"def":"One who sells distilled liquors by the dram or glass.","pos":""}],"DRAMSHOP":[{"def":"A shop or barroom where spirits are sold by the dram.","pos":""}],"DRANK":[{"def":"Wild oats, or darnel grass.","pos":""}],"DRAP D'ETE":[{"def":"A thin woolen fabric, twilled like merino.","pos":""}],"DRAPE":[{"def":"To cover or adorn with drapery or folds of cloth, or as with drapery; as, to drape a bust, a building, etc.","pos":""},{"def":"To rail at; to banter.","pos":""}],"DRAPER":[{"def":"One who sells cloths; a dealer in cloths; as, a draper and tailor.","pos":""}],"DRAPERIED":[{"def":"Covered or supplied with drapery.","pos":""}],"DRAPERY":[{"def":"The occupation of a draper; cloth-making, or dealing in cloth.","pos":""},{"def":"Cloth, or woolen stuffs in general.","pos":""}],"DRASTIC":[{"def":"Acting rapidly and violently; efficacious; powerful; -- opposed to bland; as, drastic purgatives.","pos":""},{"def":"A violent purgative.","pos":""}],"DRASTY":[{"def":"Filthy; worthless.","pos":""}],"DRAUGHT":[{"def":"The act of selecting or detaching soldiers; a draft (see Draft, n.","pos":""},{"def":"The force drawn; a detachment; -- in this sense usually written draft.","pos":""}],"DRAUGHTBOARD":[{"def":"A checkered board on which draughts are played.","pos":""}],"DRAUGHTHOUSE":[{"def":"A house for the reception of waste matter; a privy.","pos":""}],"DRAUGHTS":[{"def":"A mild vesicatory.","pos":""}],"DRAUGHTSMAN":[{"def":"One who draws pleadings or other writings.","pos":""},{"def":"One who draws plans and sketches of machinery, structures, and places; also, more generally, one who makes drawings of any kind.","pos":""}],"DRAUGHTSMANSHIP":[{"def":"The office, art, or work of a draughtsman.","pos":""}],"DRAUGHTY":[{"def":"Pertaining to a draught, or current of air; as, a draughtly, comfortless room.","pos":""}],"DRAVE":[{"def":"Drave Defn: , old imp.","pos":""}],"DRAVIDA":[{"def":"A race Hindostan, believed to be the original people who occupied the land before the Hindoo or Aryan invasion.","pos":""}],"DRAVIDIAN":[{"def":"Of or pertaining to the Dravida.","pos":""}],"DRAW":[{"def":"To cause to move continuously by force applied in advance of the thing moved; to pull along; to haul; to drag; to cause to follow.","pos":""},{"def":"To influence to move or tend toward one's self; to exercise an attracting force upon; to call towards itself; to attract; hence, to entice; to allure; to induce.","pos":""}],"DRAW-CUT":[{"def":"A single cut with a knife.","pos":""}],"DRAWABLE":[{"def":"Capable of being drawn.","pos":""}],"DRAWBACK":[{"def":"Money paid back or remitted; especially, a certain amount of duties or customs, sometimes the whole, and sometimes only a part, remitted or paid back by the government, on the exportation of the commodities on which they were levied.","pos":""}],"DRAWBENCH":[{"def":"A machine in which strips of metal are drawn through a drawplate; especially, one in which wire is thus made; -- also called drawing bench.","pos":""}],"DRAWBORE":[{"def":"A hole bored through a tenon nearer to the shoulder than the holes through the cheeks are to the edge or abutment against which the shoulder is to rest, so that a pin or bolt, when driven into it, will draw these parts together.","pos":""}],"DRAWBOY":[{"def":"A boy who operates the harness cords of a hand loom; also, a part of power loom that performs the same office.","pos":""}],"DRAWBRIDGE":[{"def":"A bridge of which either the whole or a part is made to be raised up, let down, or drawn or turned aside, to admit or hinder communication at pleasure, as before the gate of a town or castle, or over a navigable river or canal.","pos":""}],"DRAWCANSIR":[{"def":"A blustering, bullying fellow; a pot-valiant braggart; a bully.","pos":""}],"DRAWEE":[{"def":"The person on whom an order or bill of exchange is drawn; -- the correlative of drawer.","pos":""}],"DRAWER":[{"def":"An under-garment worn on the lower limbs.","pos":""}],"DRAWFILING":[{"def":"The process of smooth filing by working the file sidewise instead of lengthwise.","pos":""}],"DRAWGEAR":[{"def":"The means or parts by which cars are connected to be drawn.","pos":""}],"DRAWGLOVES":[{"def":"An old game, played by holding up the fingers.","pos":""}],"DRAWHEAD":[{"def":"The flanged outer end of a drawbar; also, a name applied to the drawgear.","pos":""}],"DRAWING":[{"def":"The process of pulling out and elongating the sliver from the carding machine, by revolving rollers, to prepare it for spinning.","pos":""},{"def":"A tool used for the purpose of making an incision along the path a saw is to follow, to prevent it from tearing the surface of the wood.","pos":""}],"DRAWING-ROOM":[{"def":"A room appropriated for the reception of company; a room to which company withdraws from the dining room.","pos":""},{"def":"The company assembled in such a room; also, a reception of company in it; as, to hold a drawing-room.","pos":""}],"DRAWL":[{"def":"To utter in a slow, lengthened tone.","pos":""}],"DRAWLATCH":[{"def":"A housebreaker or thief.","pos":""}],"DRAWLING":[{"def":"The act of speaking with a drawl; a drawl.","pos":""}],"DRAWLINK":[{"def":"Same as Drawbar (b).","pos":""}],"DRAWLOOM":[{"def":"A kind of loom used in weaving figured patterns; -- called also drawboy.","pos":""},{"def":"A species of damask made on the drawloom.","pos":""}],"DRAWNET":[{"def":"A net for catching the larger sorts of birds; also, a dragnet.","pos":""}],"DRAWPLATE":[{"def":"A hardened steel plate having a hole, or a gradation of conical holes, through which wires are drawn to be reduced and elongated.","pos":""}],"DRAWROD":[{"def":"A rod which unites the drawgear at opposite ends of the car, and bears the pull required to draw the train.","pos":""}],"DRAWSHAVE":[{"def":"See Drawing knife.","pos":""}],"DRAWSPRING":[{"def":"The spring to which a drawbar is attached.","pos":""}],"DRAY":[{"def":"A squirrel's nest.","pos":""}],"DRAYAGE":[{"def":"The charge, or sum paid, for the use of a dray.","pos":""}],"DRAYMAN":[{"def":"A man who attends a dray.","pos":""}],"DRAZEL":[{"def":"A slut; a vagabond wench.","pos":""}]}